President Cyril Ramaphosa will be delivering a plan on how nations around the world can overcome the COVID-19 pandemic and restore economic growth and jobs. He is partaking in the virtual summit of G20 nations. In a draft communique, the G20 nations have reiterated their commitment to continue doing everything possible to contain the COVID-19 pandemic, warning that the global economic recovery remains “uneven, highly uncertain, and subject to elevated downside risks”. Below is the stream:   